title: Malay Chicken Curry Kebabs
summary: The recipe Malay Chicken Curry Kebabs is ready in about 32 minutes and is definitely a great gluten free option for lovers of Indian food. This recipe makes 6 servings with 436 calories, 20g of protein, and 27g of fat each. For $1.62 per serving, this recipe covers 14% of your daily requirements of vitamins and minerals. It works well as a main course. 1 person has made this recipe and would make it again. A mixture of salt and freshly cracked pepper, celery, worcester sauce, and a handful of other ingredients are all it takes to make this recipe so tasty. To use up the table sugar you could follow this main course with the Strawberry-Lavender Shortcakes as a dessert. All things considered, we decided this recipe deserves a spoonacular score of 41%. This score is good. Try Bo-Kaap Cape Malay Kerrie - South African Cape Malay Curry, Malay-Style Red Chicken Curry, and Cape Malay Curry for similar recipes.

winePairing.pairingText: Riesling, Gewurztraminer, and Chenin Blanc are my top picks for Asian. The best wine for Asian food depends on the cuisine and dish - of course - but these acidic whites pair with a number of traditional meals, spicy or not. One wine you could try is Fess Parker Santa Barbara Riesling. It has 4.1 out of 5 stars and a bottle costs about 15 dollars.

productMatches.title: Fess Parker Santa Barbara Riesling
productMatches.description: Floral notes and orange blossoms, commingle with scents of citrus, peach, honeysuckle and light apricot on the nose. On the palate you will find flavors of peach, apricot and citrus. These flavors combine to produce an off-dry, yet well-balanced Riesling.
